<div class="max-w-xl mx-auto p-8">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Transaction Kind Selector (Real-World Example)</h2>

  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
    This is how the component is used in the actual transaction form - compact, mobile-friendly, with radio button behavior.
  </p>

  <div class="mb-4 p-3 bg-blue-50 rounded text-sm space-y-1">
    <div><strong>Configuration:</strong></div>
    <div>â€¢ <code>compact: true</code> - Smaller, horizontal layout</div>
    <div>â€¢ <code>multiple: false</code> - Only one kind can be selected</div>
    <div>â€¢ <code>show_visual_checkbox: false</code> - No checkbox icon</div>
    <div>â€¢ <code>additional_classes: 'kind-card'</code> - Custom styling (centered text)</div>
  </div>

  <%= form_with url: "#", method: :post, class: "space-y-6" do |form| %>
    <!-- Kind Selector -->
    <div>
      <label class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2">Transaction Kind</label>
      <div class="flex gap-2">
        <%= render Ui::SelectableCardComponent.new(
          item: { name: "Expense", value: "expense", description: "Money you spend" },
          form: form,
          field: :kind,
          selected: true,
          compact: true,
          multiple: false,
          show_visual_checkbox: false,
          additional_classes: 'kind-card'
        ) %>

        <%= render Ui::SelectableCardComponent.new(
          item: { name: "Income", value: "income", description: "Money you receive" },
          form: form,
          field: :kind,
          selected: false,
          compact: true,
          multiple: false,
          show_visual_checkbox: false,
          additional_classes: 'kind-card'
        ) %>

        <%= render Ui::SelectableCardComponent.new(
          item: { name: "Loan", value: "loan", description: "Money you lend" },
          form: form,
          field: :kind,
          selected: false,
          compact: true,
          multiple: false,
          show_visual_checkbox: false,
          additional_classes: 'kind-card'
        ) %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Amount Field (example) -->
    <div>
      <label class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2">Amount</label>
      <input type="number" class="w-full px-3 py-2 border border-gray-300 rounded-md" placeholder="0.00" step="0.01" />
    </div>

    <!-- Submit Button -->
    <div>
      <button type="submit" class="w-full px-4 py-3 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-md hover:bg-blue-700 font-medium">
        Save Transaction
      </button>
    </div>
  <% end %>

  <div class="mt-6 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded">
    <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Benefits of this approach:</h4>
    <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
      <li>ðŸ“± <strong>Mobile-friendly:</strong> Compact horizontal layout saves space</li>
      <li>ðŸŽ¯ <strong>Clear selection:</strong> Radio behavior prevents multiple selections</li>
      <li>âœ¨ <strong>Clean UI:</strong> No visual checkboxes, just selected state styling</li>
      <li>ðŸŽ¨ <strong>Customizable:</strong> Additional classes for centering text</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .kind-card {
    text-align: center;
    min-width: 100px;
  }

  .kind-card h4 {
    padding-left: 1px;
    padding-right: 1px;
  }
